[{"emoji":"👍","reasoning":"The goal of this sequence is to replicate a casual, confident 'thumbs up' gesture, keeping in mind the robot doesn't have thumbs, but I can imply a thumbs up facing the palm inward and gesturing upward. I'll begin by keeping both arms relaxed at the sides and will gradually bring the right arm up to form the best approximation of a thumbs up gesture using the two shoulder-like joints. Checking examples will ensure smooth transitions and alignment. In the first frame, both arms remain casually at the sides, with the shoulders slightly raised and palms facing backward. This neutral posture creates an 'engaged but relaxed' stance, setting the stage for movement. In the second frame, the right arm begins to rise forward, with the wrist facing downward. The left arm remains at rest to create balance. This pause in motion allows for a brief moment of anticipation, as if deciding whether to give a thumbs up. By the third frame, the right wrist rotates inward, mimicking the shift toward a 'thumbs up' position. The right arm lifts slightly higher to begin emphasizing the gesture. Moving into the fourth frame, the right arm rises further and the wrist twists slightly to emphasize the thumbs up even more. This movement accentuates the gesture's positive intent. In the final frame, the right arm is raised to its peak, with the wrist oriented to mimic the thumbs-up gesture as much as possible given the robot’s hand constraints. The left arm remains still throughout to maintain symmetry and ensure that the attention is focused on the right arm’s movement.","frames":[[{"state":"ArmPose","parameters":{"side":"left","joint1":15.0,"joint2":-90.0,"wrist":90.0}},{"state":"ArmPose","parameters":{"side":"right","joint1":15.0,"joint2":-90.0,"wrist":90.0}}],[{"state":"ArmPose","parameters":{"side":"left","joint1":0.0,"joint2":-80.0,"wrist":0.0}},{"state":"ArmPose","parameters":{"side":"right","joint1":0.0,"joint2":-20.0,"wrist":90.0}}],[{"state":"ArmPose","parame